This paper is primarily focused on the development and evaluation of a methodology and framework for efficient and effective real-time malware detection, leveraging machine learning and deep learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel deep learning algorithm for malware detection, which suggests a potential fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the application of delays in software subjected to ML, which could be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
